ed by the regex!)\n     - Wait, ż is not in [a-zA-Z] range! So letters = \"maonazielonafasolka\"... wait let me be more careful.\n     - \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" - the chars: S, m, a, ż, o, n, a, (space), z, i, e, l, o, n, a, (space), f, a, s, o, l, k, a\n     - After `/[^a-zA-Z]/g` removal: S, m, a, o, n, a, z, i, e, l, o, n, a, f, a, s, o, l, k, a (ż is removed)\n     - letters = \"Smaonazielonafasolka\" (20 chars)\n     - letters.length = 20, >= 2 ✓\n     - vowels check: a,o,a,i,e,o,a,a,o,a = 10 vowels out of 20 = 0.5 → within 0.10-0.85 ✓\n     - Single word check: 3 words, not 1 ✓\n     - `lowercase→uppercase transition`: not single word ✓\n     - `starts with lowercase`: \"Smażona\" starts with S (uppercase) ✓\n     - `. followed by letter`: no ✓\n     - Multi-word garbled check: words = [\"Smażona\", \"zielona\", \"fasolka\"]\n       - \"Smażona\": starts with S (uppercase), not /^[a-z]/ → skip\n       - \"zielona\": /^[a-z]/ matches (starts with z lowercase). `w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\")` = \"zielona\" = 7 chars. 7 > 2, so this word is NOT garbled.\n       - \"fasolka\": /^[a-z]/ matches. `w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\")` = \"fasolka\" = 7 chars. 7 > 2, so not garbled.\n     - Returns false (not garbled) ✓\n   - not cooking instruction ✓ (3 words, < 4 required)\n   - no pipe ✓\n   - no trailing page number ✓\n   - no double slash ✓\n   - no bullet ✓\n   - no \"For the\" ✓\n   - no trailing colon ✓\n   - not section label ✓\n   - not single non-title word ✓\n   - words.length = 3, < 8 ✓\n   - PASSES! Returns true.\n\nSo the candidate DOES pass hard filters. Now let me think about what happens in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings`.\n\nThe candidates include \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" (position 0, single), \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" (position 1, single, ALL_CAPS), and likely some multi-line joins.\n\nWait - let me also check the 2-line join of line 0 + line 1: \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"\nAnd line 0 + line 1 + line 2: \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM 그린빈 볶음\"\n\nThese would also be checked through passesHardFilters.\n\nFor the 3-line join \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM 그린빈 볶음\":\n- This has ≥8 words? \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM 그린빈 볶음\" = 8 words\n- And no separator... so it would be filtered by `words.length >= 8 && !/ [+:&/] /.test(text)`\n- Wait, does it pass? 8 >= 8 = true, and no separator... so FAILS hard filter.\n\nFor the 2-line join \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\":\n- 6 words, passes word count check\n- But `isLikelyGarbled` check: `. followed by letter` - no. Multi-word garbled check: no lowercase garbled words.\n- Should pass.\n\nNow in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings`, the bilingual detection logic:\n- `prePos0 = scored.find((s) => s.position === 0 && !isAllCaps(s.text))`\n  - \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" at position 0, not ALL_CAPS → matches\n- `nearbyAllCaps = scored.filter((s) => isAllCaps(s.text) && s.position >= 1 && s.position <= 2 && s.origin === \"single\")`\n  - \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" at position 1, ALL_CAPS, single → matches\n- Embedding similarity check between \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" and \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\":\n  - These are semantically similar (both mean \"fried green beans\") → likely > 0.4\n  - So \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" is tagged as a translation candidate\n\nThen `scoredForThreshold` removes candidates that contain the translation:\n- \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" removed\n- \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" (2-line join) → ends with the translation → removed\n- Any 3-line join containing it → removed\n\nThen structuralHeading: \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" was the structural heading (ALL_CAPS, ≥2 words, each ≥4 alpha letters). But it's identified as translation, so the structural heading gets reassigned.\n\nAfter removing translations, `scoredForThreshold` should still contain \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" at position 0.\n\nNow the threshold: `bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map((s) => s.thresholdScore))`\n\nWait - what OTHER candidates survive? Let me think...\n- Line 3: \"Wymyslitem ten pireepis, gøy zomleszkotam we francji Laczy or amul kaneolckle i fanciste\" - this is very long, ≥8 words → filtered\n- Line 4: \"Maj migz, ktöry Jest Froncuzem, przepode zo to fenelike.\" - has `. ` followed by letter? No, ends with period. But `isLikelyGarbled`: \". \" followed by letter? It ends with \"fenelike.\" - no space after period. But wait: \"ktöry Jest Froncuzem, przepode zo to fenelike.\" - is there a \". \" in the middle? No. But it has 8+ words? \"Maj migz ktöry Jest Froncuzem przepode zo to fenelike\" = 9 words → filtered by ≥8 rule.\n- Line 5: \"DLA & OSOB\" → matches METADATA_PATTERNS: `/^DLA\\s+[^a-zA-Z0-9\\s]\\s/i` where & is non-alphanumeric → `looksLikeMetadata` → filtered\n- Line 6: \"Przvgetowanie\" → close to \"przygotowanie\" but with OCR errors. `isSectionLabel`: after stripping diacritics... \"przvgetowanie\" - this doesn't match \"przygotowanie\" → might pass. But `isLikelyGarbled`: single word, unicode letters = \"Przvgetowanie\" = 13 chars > 3, not garbled. So it might become a candidate.\n- Line 7: \"15 minut\" → starts with number → filtered\n- Line 8: \"Smazenie 15 minut\" → matches metadata pattern `/\\b\\d+\\s*MIN\\b/i` → filtered\n- Line 9: \"SKLADNIKI\" → section label → filtered\n- Line 10+: ingredients\n\nSo the surviving candidates in `scoredForThreshold` are likely:\n1. \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" (position 0)\n2. Maybe \"Przvgetowanie\" (position 6)  \n3. Maybe some multi-line joins\n\nThe issue might be that \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" has a LOW rawScore. The embedding comparison:\n- titleSim: how similar is \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" to \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\"?\n- headerSim: how similar to \"ingredients list, cooking directions...\"?\n- noiseSim: how similar to \"page number, table of contents...\"?\n\nPolish title text should have decent similarity to the Polish reference strings \"nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\". But \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" literally means \"Fried green beans\" - it's a food name, not semantically similar to \"recipe name\" or \"dish title\". The embedding model might give it a moderate titleSim.\n\nThe rawScore = titleSim - max(headerSim, noiseSim). If this is very low (near 0 or negative), and the threshold is `max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7)`, it might not pass.\n\nBut wait - let me look at the `selected.length === 0` fallback path:\n```\nif (selected.length === 0 && scored.length > 0) {\n    const fallback = scored.slice().sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position || b.score - a.score);\n    if (fallback[0].rawScore > 0.02) {\n      selected = [fallback[0]];\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIf rawScore <= 0.02, even the fallback won't fire, and the function returns undefined.\n\nThat's probably the issue! \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" likely has a very low rawScore (maybe even negative), so nothing survives the threshold AND the fallback's 0.02 check.\n\nActually wait - I need to reconsider. The bilingual detection logic suppresses the translation from `scoredForThreshold`, but the THRESHOLD is computed from `scoredForThreshold`. If only \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" and maybe \"Przvgetowanie\" remain, and both have low rawScores, the threshold might still be achievable. \n\nThe most likely scenario: \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" has a rawScore that's low enough to fail even the relaxed threshold, AND the fallback's 0.02 minimum also rejects it. Result: empty output.\n\nThe fix should be: add a last-resort fallback that returns the first non-empty line when everything else fails. This is exactly what the feedback recommends.\n\nTell me if this analysis makes sense."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9268,"cache_read_input_tokens":63262,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9268},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier"