{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Eivvc3D3p585pU1bkFWWHJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There it is. That is the smoking gun.\n\n## Analysis Summary\n\n**Problem**: \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" returns empty from `extractTitleWithEmbeddings`.\n\n**Severity**: High -- complete extraction failure on a valid, unambiguous recipe title.\n\n**Root Cause**: The embedding model rates \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" with a `rawScore` of **0.0002** -- effectively zero. The `titleSim` (0.4140) and `headerSim` (0.4138) are nearly identical, so the differential signal is negligible.\n\n**Precise failure chain**:\n\nYour trace is correct in almost every detail. Here is the confirmed chain with the actual numbers:\n\n### Step 1: Candidates pass hard filters correctly\n\n\"Smazona zielona fasolka\" at position 0 passes all hard filters. Your `isLikelyGarbled` trace is accurate -- `letters = \"Smaonazielonafasolka\"` (20 chars), vowel ratio 0.5, no garbled words. \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" at position 1 also passes. \"Przvgetowanie\" at position 6 also passes (it is not in `SECTION_LABELS` because the OCR-corrupted form does not match \"przygotowanie\" after diacritic stripping -- `stripDiacritics(\"Przvgetowanie\")` yields \"Przvgetowanie\" which differs from \"przygotowanie\").\n\n### Step 2: Bilingual detection fires correctly\n\n- `prePos0` = \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" (position 0, not ALL_CAPS)\n- `nearbyAllCaps` = [\"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"] (position 1, ALL_CAPS, single)\n- Embedding similarity between the Polish title and the English translation: this likely exceeds 0.4 (both are about green beans), so \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" becomes a `translationCandidate`\n- `scoredForThreshold` removes \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" and the 2-line join\n\n### Step 3: Threshold computation kills everything\n\nAfter translation removal, `scoredForThreshold` contains:\n- \"Smazona zielona fasolka\": `thresholdScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus = 0.0002 + 0.0 = 0.0002`\n- \"Przvgetowanie\": `thresholdScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus = 0.0700 + 0.0 = 0.0700`\n\n`bestThresholdScore = 0.0700`  \n`threshold = Math.max(0.08, 0.0700 * 0.7) = Math.max(0.08, 0.049) = 0.08`\n\nThe threshold floor of **0.08** is the killer.\n\nNow, \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" has a score of approximately `0.0002 * positionFactor + 0 + 0 ≈ 0.0002`. This is far below 0.08. \"Przvgetowanie\" has a score of approximately 0.07 (with position factor). Also below 0.08.\n\n**Nothing passes the threshold.** `selected` is empty.\n\n### Step 4: Fallback also fails\n\nThe fallback at line ~960:\n```typescript\nif (selected.length === 0 && scored.length > 0) {\n    const fallback = scored.slice().sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position || b.score - a.score);\n    if (fallback[0].rawScore > 0.02) {\n      selected = [fallback[0]];\n    }\n}\n```\n\n`fallback[0]` is \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" (position 0). Its `rawScore` is **0.0002**, which is NOT greater than 0.02. The fallback guard rejects it. Result: `undefined`.\n\n### Why the embedding fails\n\nThe embedding model sees \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" (Polish for \"Fried green beans\") as almost equally similar to `TITLE_REFERENCE` (\"recipe name, dish title...\") and `HEADER_REFERENCE` (\"ingredients list, cooking directions...\"). The differential `titleSim - headerSim = 0.4140 - 0.4138 = 0.0002` is essentially noise. This is a fundamental limitation of the small embedding model: Polish food names are not distinctive enough from Polish cooking vocabulary in the embedding space.\n\nMeanwhile \"Przvgetowanie\" (OCR-garbled \"Przygotowanie\" = \"Preparation\") scores better because it is closer to the header reference but gets a higher titleSim too -- the model sees it as a section heading, which is more distinctive than a generic food name.\n\n### The fix\n\nYour analysis correctly identifies the solution. There are two reasonable approaches:\n\n**Option A (minimal, as recommended by the iteration feedback)**: Add a last-resort fallback in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` that returns the first non-blank line when everything else fails. At `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` around line 1137, before the final `return undefined`, add:\n\n```typescript\n// Last resort: return first non-blank line that passes hard filters\nconst firstNonBlank = lines.find(l => l.trim().length > 0 && passesHardFilters(l.trim()));\nif (firstNonBlank) return normalizeOcrTitle(firstNonBlank.trim().normalize(\"NFC\"));\n```\n\n**Option B (targeted)**: Lower the fallback rawScore threshold from 0.02 to something like -0.05 or 0.0, since the candidate did legitimately pass all hard filters and sits at position 0. The 0.02 guard was designed to prevent ingredient-line leakage, but a position-0 candidate that passed hard filters is extremely unlikely to be an ingredient line.\n\nOption A is safer and more general. Option B is more surgical but risks edge-case regressions.\n\n### Key files\n\n- `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` -- lines 205-210 (`isLikelyGarbled`), lines 310-320 (`passesHardFilters`), lines 820-840 (bilingual detection), lines 885-895 (threshold computation), lines 955-965 (fallback guard with 0.02 threshold)\n- `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Smażona zielona fasolka.real.txt` -- the failing input"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa8d3d7148c726255 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 55990\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 174400</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c607690-947d-4a99-99f9-d42643539da8","uuid":"54fe9c20-e39e-4f90-bb08-e42ca850036e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need you to trace through the title extraction code to understand exactly why \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" returns empty.\n\nThe input file has these lines:\n```\nLine 0: Smażona zielona fasolka\nLine 1: GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\nLine 2: 그린빈 볶음\nLine 3: Wymyslitem ten pireepis, gøy zomleszkotam we francji Laczy or amul kaneolckle i fanciste\nLine 4: Maj migz, ktöry Jest Froncuzem, przepode zo to fenelike.\nLine 5: DLA & OSOB\nLine 6: Przvgetowanie\nLine 7: 15 minut\nLine 8: Smazenie 15 minut\nLine 9: SKLADNIKI\nLine 10: 500 g cienkiej zielonej\nLine 11: fasolk\n...\n```\n\nKey functions to trace through:\n\n1. `buildCandidates` processes non-empty lines. The `findBurstEnd` function checks for garbled lines at the start.\n\n2. `isLikelyGarbled(\"그린빈 볶음\")` - The Korean text. Let's check:\n   - `letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\")` → empty string (Korean chars are not a-zA-Z)\n   - `letters.length < 2` → `0 < 2` → TRUE → returns true (garbled)\n   \n   OK so Korean line is filtered as garbled. But it's line index 2, and \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" is index 0.\n\n3. For `findBurstEnd`: it checks `while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text) && !isAllCaps(lines[i].text))`. \n   - Line 0: \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" has length 22, which is >= 20, so burst end stays at 0.\n   \n4. So candidates should include line 0. Let's check `passesHardFilters(\"Smażona zielona fasolka\")`:\n   - length 22, within 3-80 ✓\n   - not ingredient ✓\n   - not starts with number ✓ \n   - not metadata ✓\n   - `isLikelyGarbled(\"Smażona zielona fasolka\")`:\n     - `letters = \"Smaonazielonafalka\"` (after removing non a-zA-Z chars - NOTE: ż is removed by the regex!)\n     - Wait, ż is not in [a-zA-Z] range! So letters = \"maonazielonafasolka\"... wait let me be more careful.\n     - \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" - the chars: S, m, a, ż, o, n, a, (space), z, i, e, l, o, n, a, (space), f, a, s, o, l, k, a\n     - After `/[^a-zA-Z]/g` removal: S, m, a, o, n, a, z, i, e, l, o, n, a, f, a, s, o, l, k, a (ż is removed)\n     - letters = \"Smaonazielonafasolka\" (20 chars)\n     - letters.length = 20, >= 2 ✓\n     - vowels check: a,o,a,i,e,o,a,a,o,a = 10 vowels out of 20 = 0.5 → within 0.10-0.85 ✓\n     - Single word check: 3 words, not 1 ✓\n     - `lowercase→uppercase transition`: not single word ✓\n     - `starts with lowercase`: \"Smażona\" starts with S (uppercase) ✓\n     - `. followed by letter`: no ✓\n     - Multi-word garbled check: words = [\"Smażona\", \"zielona\", \"fasolka\"]\n       - \"Smażona\": starts with S (uppercase), not /^[a-z]/ → skip\n       - \"zielona\": /^[a-z]/ matches (starts with z lowercase). `w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\")` = \"zielona\" = 7 chars. 7 > 2, so this word is NOT garbled.\n       - \"fasolka\": /^[a-z]/ matches. `w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\")` = \"fasolka\" = 7 chars. 7 > 2, so not garbled.\n     - Returns false (not garbled) ✓\n   - not cooking instruction ✓ (3 words, < 4 required)\n   - no pipe ✓\n   - no trailing page number ✓\n   - no double slash ✓\n   - no bullet ✓\n   - no \"For the\" ✓\n   - no trailing colon ✓\n   - not section label ✓\n   - not single non-title word ✓\n   - words.length = 3, < 8 ✓\n   - PASSES! Returns true.\n\nSo the candidate DOES pass hard filters. Now let me think about what happens in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings`.\n\nThe candidates include \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" (position 0, single), \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" (position 1, single, ALL_CAPS), and likely some multi-line joins.\n\nWait - let me also check the 2-line join of line 0 + line 1: \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"\nAnd line 0 + line 1 + line 2: \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM 그린빈 볶음\"\n\nThese would also be checked through passesHardFilters.\n\nFor the 3-line join \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM 그린빈 볶음\":\n- This has ≥8 words? \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM 그린빈 볶음\" = 8 words\n- And no separator... so it would be filtered by `words.length >= 8 && !/ [+:&/] /.test(text)`\n- Wait, does it pass? 8 >= 8 = true, and no separator... so FAILS hard filter.\n\nFor the 2-line join \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\":\n- 6 words, passes word count check\n- But `isLikelyGarbled` check: `. followed by letter` - no. Multi-word garbled check: no lowercase garbled words.\n- Should pass.\n\nNow in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings`, the bilingual detection logic:\n- `prePos0 = scored.find((s) => s.position === 0 && !isAllCaps(s.text))`\n  - \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" at position 0, not ALL_CAPS → matches\n- `nearbyAllCaps = scored.filter((s) => isAllCaps(s.text) && s.position >= 1 && s.position <= 2 && s.origin === \"single\")`\n  - \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" at position 1, ALL_CAPS, single → matches\n- Embedding similarity check between \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" and \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\":\n  - These are semantically similar (both mean \"fried green beans\") → likely > 0.4\n  - So \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" is tagged as a translation candidate\n\nThen `scoredForThreshold` removes candidates that contain the translation:\n- \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" removed\n- \"Smażona zielona fasolka GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" (2-line join) → ends with the translation → removed\n- Any 3-line join containing it → removed\n\nThen structuralHeading: \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" was the structural heading (ALL_CAPS, ≥2 words, each ≥4 alpha letters). But it's identified as translation, so the structural heading gets reassigned.\n\nAfter removing translations, `scoredForThreshold` should still contain \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" at position 0.\n\nNow the threshold: `bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map((s) => s.thresholdScore))`\n\nWait - what OTHER candidates survive? Let me think...\n- Line 3: \"Wymyslitem ten pireepis, gøy zomleszkotam we francji Laczy or amul kaneolckle i fanciste\" - this is very long, ≥8 words → filtered\n- Line 4: \"Maj migz, ktöry Jest Froncuzem, przepode zo to fenelike.\" - has `. ` followed by letter? No, ends with period. But `isLikelyGarbled`: \". \" followed by letter? It ends with \"fenelike.\" - no space after period. But wait: \"ktöry Jest Froncuzem, przepode zo to fenelike.\" - is there a \". \" in the middle? No. But it has 8+ words? \"Maj migz ktöry Jest Froncuzem przepode zo to fenelike\" = 9 words → filtered by ≥8 rule.\n- Line 5: \"DLA & OSOB\" → matches METADATA_PATTERNS: `/^DLA\\s+[^a-zA-Z0-9\\s]\\s/i` where & is non-alphanumeric → `looksLikeMetadata` → filtered\n- Line 6: \"Przvgetowanie\" → close to \"przygotowanie\" but with OCR errors. `isSectionLabel`: after stripping diacritics... \"przvgetowanie\" - this doesn't match \"przygotowanie\" → might pass. But `isLikelyGarbled`: single word, unicode letters = \"Przvgetowanie\" = 13 chars > 3, not garbled. So it might become a candidate.\n- Line 7: \"15 minut\" → starts with number → filtered\n- Line 8: \"Smazenie 15 minut\" → matches metadata pattern `/\\b\\d+\\s*MIN\\b/i` → filtered\n- Line 9: \"SKLADNIKI\" → section label → filtered\n- Line 10+: ingredients\n\nSo the surviving candidates in `scoredForThreshold` are likely:\n1. \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" (position 0)\n2. Maybe \"Przvgetowanie\" (position 6)  \n3. Maybe some multi-line joins\n\nThe issue might be that \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" has a LOW rawScore. The embedding comparison:\n- titleSim: how similar is \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" to \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\"?\n- headerSim: how similar to \"ingredients list, cooking directions...\"?\n- noiseSim: how similar to \"page number, table of contents...\"?\n\nPolish title text should have decent similarity to the Polish reference strings \"nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\". But \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" literally means \"Fried green beans\" - it's a food name, not semantically similar to \"recipe name\" or \"dish title\". The embedding model might give it a moderate titleSim.\n\nThe rawScore = titleSim - max(headerSim, noiseSim). If this is very low (near 0 or negative), and the threshold is `max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7)`, it might not pass.\n\nBut wait - let me look at the `selected.length === 0` fallback path:\n```\nif (selected.length === 0 && scored.length > 0) {\n    const fallback = scored.slice().sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position || b.score - a.score);\n    if (fallback[0].rawScore > 0.02) {\n      selected = [fallback[0]];\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIf rawScore <= 0.02, even the fallback won't fire, and the function returns undefined.\n\nThat's probably the issue! \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" likely has a very low rawScore (maybe even negative), so nothing survives the threshold AND the fallback's 0.02 check.\n\nActually wait - I need to reconsider. The bilingual detection logic suppresses the translation from `scoredForThreshold`, but the THRESHOLD is computed from `scoredForThreshold`. If only \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" and maybe \"Przvgetowanie\" remain, and both have low rawScores, the threshold might still be achievable. \n\nThe most likely scenario: \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" has a rawScore that's low enough to fail even the relaxed threshold, AND the fallback's 0.02 minimum also rejects it. Result: empty output.\n\nThe fix should be: add a last-resort fallback that returns the first non-empty line when everything else fails. This is exactly what the feedback recommends.\n\nTell me if this analysis makes sense.","agentId":"aa8d3d7148c726255","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There it is. That is the smoking gun.\n\n## Analysis Summary\n\n**Problem**: \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" returns empty from `extractTitleWithEmbeddings`.\n\n**Severity**: High -- complete extraction failure on a valid, unambiguous recipe title.\n\n**Root Cause**: The embedding model rates \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" with a `rawScore` of **0.0002** -- effectively zero. The `titleSim` (0.4140) and `headerSim` (0.4138) are nearly identical, so the differential signal is negligible.\n\n**Precise failure chain**:\n\nYour trace is correct in almost every detail. Here is the confirmed chain with the actual numbers:\n\n### Step 1: Candidates pass hard filters correctly\n\n\"Smazona zielona fasolka\" at position 0 passes all hard filters. Your `isLikelyGarbled` trace is accurate -- `letters = \"Smaonazielonafasolka\"` (20 chars), vowel ratio 0.5, no garbled words. \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" at position 1 also passes. \"Przvgetowanie\" at position 6 also passes (it is not in `SECTION_LABELS` because the OCR-corrupted form does not match \"przygotowanie\" after diacritic stripping -- `stripDiacritics(\"Przvgetowanie\")` yields \"Przvgetowanie\" which differs from \"przygotowanie\").\n\n### Step 2: Bilingual detection fires correctly\n\n- `prePos0` = \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" (position 0, not ALL_CAPS)\n- `nearbyAllCaps` = [\"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\"] (position 1, ALL_CAPS, single)\n- Embedding similarity between the Polish title and the English translation: this likely exceeds 0.4 (both are about green beans), so \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" becomes a `translationCandidate`\n- `scoredForThreshold` removes \"GREEN BEANS BORKEUM\" and the 2-line join\n\n### Step 3: Threshold computation kills everything\n\nAfter translation removal, `scoredForThreshold` contains:\n- \"Smazona zielona fasolka\": `thresholdScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus = 0.0002 + 0.0 = 0.0002`\n- \"Przvgetowanie\": `thresholdScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus = 0.0700 + 0.0 = 0.0700`\n\n`bestThresholdScore = 0.0700`  \n`threshold = Math.max(0.08, 0.0700 * 0.7) = Math.max(0.08, 0.049) = 0.08`\n\nThe threshold floor of **0.08** is the killer.\n\nNow, \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" has a score of approximately `0.0002 * positionFactor + 0 + 0 ≈ 0.0002`. This is far below 0.08. \"Przvgetowanie\" has a score of approximately 0.07 (with position factor). Also below 0.08.\n\n**Nothing passes the threshold.** `selected` is empty.\n\n### Step 4: Fallback also fails\n\nThe fallback at line ~960:\n```typescript\nif (selected.length === 0 && scored.length > 0) {\n    const fallback = scored.slice().sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position || b.score - a.score);\n    if (fallback[0].rawScore > 0.02) {\n      selected = [fallback[0]];\n    }\n}\n```\n\n`fallback[0]` is \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" (position 0). Its `rawScore` is **0.0002**, which is NOT greater than 0.02. The fallback guard rejects it. Result: `undefined`.\n\n### Why the embedding fails\n\nThe embedding model sees \"Smazona zielona fasolka\" (Polish for \"Fried green beans\") as almost equally similar to `TITLE_REFERENCE` (\"recipe name, dish title...\") and `HEADER_REFERENCE` (\"ingredients list, cooking directions...\"). The differential `titleSim - headerSim = 0.4140 - 0.4138 = 0.0002` is essentially noise. This is a fundamental limitation of the small embedding model: Polish food names are not distinctive enough from Polish cooking vocabulary in the embedding space.\n\nMeanwhile \"Przvgetowanie\" (OCR-garbled \"Przygotowanie\" = \"Preparation\") scores better because it is closer to the header reference but gets a higher titleSim too -- the model sees it as a section heading, which is more distinctive than a generic food name.\n\n### The fix\n\nYour analysis correctly identifies the solution. There are two reasonable approaches:\n\n**Option A (minimal, as recommended by the iteration feedback)**: Add a last-resort fallback in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` that returns the first non-blank line when everything else fails. At `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` around line 1137, before the final `return undefined`, add:\n\n```typescript\n// Last resort: return first non-blank line that passes hard filters\nconst firstNonBlank = lines.find(l => l.trim().length > 0 && passesHardFilters(l.trim()));\nif (firstNonBlank) return normalizeOcrTitle(firstNonBlank.trim().normalize(\"NFC\"));\n```\n\n**Option B (targeted)**: Lower the fallback rawScore threshold from 0.02 to something like -0.05 or 0.0, since the candidate did legitimately pass all hard filters and sits at position 0. The 0.02 guard was designed to prevent ingredient-line leakage, but a position-0 candidate that passed hard filters is extremely unlikely to be an ingredient line.\n\nOption A is safer and more general. Option B is more surgical but risks edge-case regressions.\n\n### Key files\n\n- `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` -- lines 205-210 (`isLikelyGarbled`), lines 310-320 (`passesHardFilters`), lines 820-840 (bilingual detection), lines 885-895 (threshold computation), lines 955-965 (fallback guard with 0.02 threshold)\n- `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Smażona zielona fasolka.real.txt` -- the failing input"}],"totalDurationMs":174400,"totalTokens":55990,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":987,"cache_read_input_tokens":53387,"output_tokens":1615,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":987},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
